<item>
            <title>[SEC-2707] allow addition of a custom TokenGranter in AuthorizationServerEndpointsConfigurer</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-2707</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While configuring an OAuth AuthorizationServer with &lt;tt&gt;AuthorizationServerEndpointsConfigurer&lt;/tt&gt; it is not easy to add an additional `TokenGranter`.&lt;br/&gt;
One is able to do something like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p/&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;syntaxplugin&quot; class=&quot;syntaxplugin&quot; style=&quot;border: 1px dashed #bbb; border-radius: 5px !important; overflow: auto; max-height: 30em;&quot;&gt;
&lt;table cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot; style=&quot;font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.4em !important; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; color: black;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;tbody &gt;
				&lt;tr id=&quot;syntaxplugin_code_and_gutter&quot;&gt;
						&lt;td  style=&quot; line-height: 1.4em !important; padding: 0em; vertical-align: top;&quot;&gt;
					&lt;pre style=&quot;font-size: 1em; margin: 0 10px;  margin-top: 10px;   width: auto; padding: 0;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: black; font-family: &apos;Consolas&apos;, &apos;Bitstream Vera Sans Mono&apos;, &apos;Courier New&apos;, Courier, monospace !important;&quot;&gt;        List&amp;lt;TokenGranter&amp;gt; tokenGranters = getTokenGranters(); // implementation up to you&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
				&lt;tr id=&quot;syntaxplugin_code_and_gutter&quot;&gt;
						&lt;td  style=&quot; line-height: 1.4em !important; padding: 0em; vertical-align: top;&quot;&gt;
					&lt;pre style=&quot;font-size: 1em; margin: 0 10px;   width: auto; padding: 0;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: black; font-family: &apos;Consolas&apos;, &apos;Bitstream Vera Sans Mono&apos;, &apos;Courier New&apos;, Courier, monospace !important;&quot;&gt;        tokenGranter = new CompositeTokenGranter(tokenGranters);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
				&lt;tr id=&quot;syntaxplugin_code_and_gutter&quot;&gt;
						&lt;td  style=&quot; line-height: 1.4em !important; padding: 0em; vertical-align: top;&quot;&gt;
					&lt;pre style=&quot;font-size: 1em; margin: 0 10px;   margin-bottom: 10px;  width: auto; padding: 0;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: black; font-family: &apos;Consolas&apos;, &apos;Bitstream Vera Sans Mono&apos;, &apos;Courier New&apos;, Courier, monospace !important;&quot;&gt;        endpoints.tokenGranter(tokenGranter);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p/&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but the problem is to get hold of the default `TokenGranter`s, if one gets them via &lt;tt&gt;AuthorizationServerSecurityConfigurer.getTokenGranter()&lt;/tt&gt; then they are not initialized correctly, as e.g. &lt;tt&gt;yooture.web.config.SecurityOauth2Configuration.AuthorizationServerConfiguration.configure(ClientDetailsServiceConfigurer)&lt;/tt&gt; has not been called yet. And cresting the defaults from scratch raises some other issues on how to get hold on the required references used to create these.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So this feature request asks for a proper way on how to configure/add a custom &lt;tt&gt;TokenGranter&lt;/tt&gt; via Spring Java Config.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
